public abstract class If_acmp
extends GeneralInstructionWithOtherBytes
implements JumpConditional, StackPop, VariableUsing

Abstract instruction with some concrete methods for comparison instructions of the group if_cmp<cond>. Concrete instructions can be extended from this class.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-11
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Constructor Detail

If_acmp

public If_acmp(AttributeCode code,
               int lineNumber)
        throws InvalidInstructionInitialisationException
Standard constructor. For the extraction of the other bytes, the attribute_code of the method that the instruction belongs to is supplied as an argument. Also the line number is given as an argument, since it is needed in case of jumping.

Parameters:
code - The attribute_code of the method that the instruction belongs to.
lineNumber - The line number of this instruction (including other bytes!).
Throws:
InvalidInstructionInitialisationException - If the instruction could not be initialized successfully, most likely due to missing additional bytes. This might be caused by a corrupt classfile, or a classfile of a more recent version than what can be handled.

getTypesPopped

public byte[] getTypesPopped(ClassFile methodClassFile)
Get the types of elements this instruction will pop from the stack.

Specified by:
getTypesPopped in interface StackPop
Parameters:
methodClassFile - The class file of the method this instruction belongs to.
Returns:
The types this instruction pops. The length of the arrays reflects the number of elements pushed in the order they are pushed. Types are ClassFile.T_BOOLEAN, ClassFile.T_BYTE ClassFile.T_CHAR, ClassFile.T_DOUBLE, ClassFile.T_FLOAT, ClassFile.T_INT, ClassFile.T_LONG and ClassFile.T_SHORT, 0 to indicate a reference or return address type or -1 to indicate the popped type cannot be determined statically.
